## 6. UX / design direction (Apple Books + Safari Reader)

- **Type:** serif body (e.g. New York / Georgia / "Iowan"), generous line-height (~1.6),
  comfortable measure (~66 chars per column).
- **Color:** off-white / warm paper background, soft grays, one restrained accent.
  Sepia and dark themes optional.
- **Chrome:** minimal. Toolbar hides while reading, reappears on hover/scroll-up
  (Safari Reader behavior).
- **Motion:** gentle, quick. No bounce, no flash.
- **The two columns** scroll together and stay paragraph-aligned.

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA target)
- Full keyboard navigation; visible focus rings.
- Real semantic HTML + ARIA where needed; screen-reader sensible.
- Contrast ≥ 4.5:1 for body text in every theme.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` and `prefers-color-scheme`.
- User-controllable font size; nothing breaks when text is enlarged 200%.

