## 8. Build stages (incremental — each stage is testable on its own)

1. **Skeleton + open EPUB** — single file opens an EPUB and shows the English text
   (one column). Proves epub.js + file loading work. *Test: I can read a book in English.*
2. **Two-column layout** — add the right column, paragraph-aligned, both always visible.
   *Test: English left, empty Chinese right, scroll together.*
3. **Live translation** — fill the right column via Google, with caching + loading states.
   *Test: Chinese appears as I read; second visit is instant.*
4. **Persistence** — IndexedDB for reading position + the translation cache.
   *Test: close & reopen, land where I left off, no re-translating.*
5. **Library / reading list** — a shelf of opened books with covers.
   *Test: my books show up; click to resume.*
6. **Translate-once-and-save mode** — full-book translation stored for offline.
   *Test: pick this mode, wait once, then read offline.*
7. **Apple polish + accessibility pass** — themes, type, focus, reduced-motion, contrast.
   *Test: looks like Apple Books; keyboard + screen reader OK.*

> Each stage produces a working file. We stop and test before the next. This is the
> "ask before large tokens" checkpoint: I approve each stage.

