## 9. How to publish on GitHub (privacy-safe)

1. New repo, e.g. `bilingual-reader`. Put ONLY `index.html` (+ vendored libs) in it.
2. Add a `.gitignore` blocking `*.epub`, `*.mobi`, and any data/backup files.
3. (Optional) Enable GitHub Pages to open it from any browser — but note: books still
   live in *that browser's* IndexedDB, so each device has its own private library.
4. Never commit a book. The repo stays a clean, shareable, empty tool.

